ope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoratio=
n: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000;=
 border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> how the company woul=
d think that</a>?</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">With the Securities and Exchange Commission pr=
eparing an enforcement action that threatens much of its business, crypto e=
xchange Coinbase is trying a novel defense. It says regulators bear some re=
sponsibility for letting the company go public in the first place.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Coinbase went public in April 2021 after clear=
ing a six-month review. SEC staff bored into its financial reporting and di=
sclosures as well as the company=E2=80=99s belief that its menu of cryptocu=
rrencies shouldn=E2=80=99t be treated as securities, which the SEC regulate=
s. Coinbase=E2=80=99s lawyers argue that by clearing the review, regulators=
 signaled that they =E2=80=9Cdid not think Coinbase=E2=80=99s core business=
 was unlawful.=E2=80=9D</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But the going-public process isn=E2=80=99t des=
igned to judge whether risks to a company=E2=80=99s future should stop it f=
rom selling shares to investors, according to securities lawyers. Other com=
panies whose business models were illegal at the federal or local level hav=
e been able to go public, including cannabis firms, gaming businesses and r=
ide-sharing companies. The SEC=E2=80=99s review solely examines how compani=
es disclose those risks to investors in their regulated filings, lawyers sa=
id.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I think that in some crude practical sense Coi=
nbase is right: If it filed to go public=C2=A0<em>today</em>, instead of in=
 2020 (for a 2021 offering), the crypto-hostile, Gary Gensler-led SEC proba=
bly=C2=A0<em>would</em> find reasons to delay its initial public=C2=A0offer=
ing indefinitely. So =E2=80=9Cthe SEC let us go public in 2021=E2=80=9D <em=
>does</em> kind of mean=C2=A0something like =E2=80=9Cthe SEC did not think =
we were totally illegal in 2021.=E2=80=9D And there is some force to the ar=
gument =E2=80=9Clook if you thought we were legal in 2021 after a thorough =
review, it seems kind of unfair for you to say we=E2=80=99re illegal and tr=
y to shut us down in 2023.=E2=80=9D</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Of course the background fact is that between =
late 2020 when Coinbase filed to go public, and early 2023 when the SEC has=
 started rumbling about a <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.co=
m/click/31392592.261430/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGl=
jbGVzLzIwMjMtMDMtMjMvdGhlLXNlYy1pcy1jb21pbmctZm9yLWNvaW5iYXNlP2NtcGlkPUJCRD=
A1MDUyM19NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJ=
nV0bV90ZXJtPTIzMDUwNSZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a=
23cB6beeaca2" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_bla=
nk" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-botto=
m-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; bac=
kground-color: #ccc;">  Coinbase enforcement action</a>, the presidential a=
dministration and the SEC=E2=80=99s leadership changed, and it is now much =
more skeptical of crypto. Coinbase <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbu=
siness.com/click/31392592.261430/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9uZXdzL3ByZXNzLX=
