c</a> three days before Gensler was <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergb=
usiness.com/click/31392592.261430/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9uZXdzL3ByZXNzL=
XJlbGVhc2UvMjAyMS02NQ/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cCbb7fbf44" itemprop=3D"StoryL=
ink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; tex=
t-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-colo=
r: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> sworn in<=
/a> at the SEC; he was just a bit too late to stop the IPO.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But=C2=A0<em>technically=C2=A0</em>nothing wor=
ks that way;=C2=A0<em>technically=C2=A0</em>the SEC never gave any official=
 approval of Coinbase=E2=80=99s business model, and=C2=A0<em>technically=C2=
=A0</em>=E2=80=9Cyou let us get away with doing illegal stuff for a few yea=
rs so you can=E2=80=99t stop us now=E2=80=9D is not a good legal argument. =
But I see why they=E2=80=99re annoyed.</p>
